#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1973
msgid "When the name of the desired option is known, one can instead press its first letter. First-letter navigation is case-insensitive.  That will then take you to the first selection starting with the pressed letter. Pressing the same letter again, will move you to the next option starting with that letter if more than one option like that exists.  Repeating the letter will cycle among all those options starting with that letter."
